statements: SELECT * FROM reinforcement_learning_models WHERE model_type = 'CNN';

SELECT model_id, model_name FROM reinforcement_learning_models WHERE performance_score < 0.5 AND model_type = 'Reinforcement Learning' ORDER BY training_time_hours ASC LIMIT 3;

SELECT * FROM models;
SELECT model_name, created_date FROM models ORDER BY created_date DESC;
SELECT model_name, performance_value FROM models LEFT JOIN performance ON models.model_id = performance.model_id;

SELECT * FROM performance WHERE performance_value > 0.9 ORDER BY recorded_date ASC;

SELECT model_id, model_name, training_episodes FROM model_performance;
SELECT model_name, training_accuracy FROM model_performance WHERE training_accuracy > 0.8;
SELECT episode_number, episode_reward, episode_length FROM episode_results ORDER BY episode_reward DESC;

SELECT model_name, model_description FROM model_performance JOIN model_metadata ON model_performance.model_id = model_metadata.model_id;
SELECT * FROM ModelPerformance;
SELECT model_id, model_name, validation_accuracy FROM ModelPerformance;
SELECT training_episodes, model_name, training_time_hours FROM ModelPerformance WHERE training_time_hours > 2;
SELECT log_id, model_id, log_timestamp FROM TrainingLogs ORDER BY log_timestamp DESC;
SELECT model_id, architecture_name, layers, nodes_per_layer FROM ModelArchitectures;
SELECT model_id, model_name, training_episodes, validation_accuracy FROM ModelPerformance ORDER BY validation_accuracy DESC, training_episodes ASC LIMIT 5;

SELECT model_name, training_time_hours, validation_accuracy FROM ModelPerformance WHERE training_time_hours > 10 AND validation_accuracy > 0.8 ORDER BY training_time_hours DESC, validation_accuracy DESC;

SELECT m.model_id, m.model_name, t.training_loss, t.validation_loss FROM ModelPerformance m INNER JOIN TrainingLogs t ON m.model_id = t.model_id WHERE t.training_loss < 0.5 OR t.validation_loss < 0.3 ORDER BY t.training_loss ASC, t.validation_loss ASC LIMIT 5;

SELECT a.model_id, a.architecture_name, a.layers, a.nodes_per_layer, m.validation_accuracy FROM ModelArchitectures a INNER JOIN ModelPerformance m ON a.model_id = m.model_id WHERE a.nodes_per_layer > 64 AND m.validation_accuracy > 0.85 ORDER BY a.nodes_per_layer DESC, m.validation_accuracy DESC;

SELECT e.model_id, e.precision, e.recall, r.resource_type, r.cpu_cores FROM EvaluationMetrics e INNER JOIN HardwareResources r ON e.model_id = r.model_id WHERE e.precision > 0.9 AND r.cpu_cores >= 8 ORDER BY e.precision DESC, r.cpu_cores DESC LIMIT 5;
